cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with interference mitigation in Wireless Body Area Networks (WBANs), which is a subfield of wireless networking and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a code allocation scheme and analyzes the success and collision probabilities of frame transmissions, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on the performance of WBANs, which is a security and privacy concern (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions power savings, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
